Activities include forestlands treated using timber sales to achieve healthier conditions; forestland vegetation improved; forestland vegetation established; vegetation improved by treatment for noxious weeds or invasive plants and hazardous fuels treated to reduce the risk of catastrophic wildland fire. These activities address the three WBBS goals: human safety, forest recovery, and long-term forest resiliency.</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>forest-service</dcat:keyword>
